pageContext.claim: “A man who's doing an incredible job as your governor, because I want to take 100% of the credit for the incredible turnaround of New Hampshire. And I remember it not so long ago, things were not looking good, people were leaving, a lot of bad things were happening, but we have to give him a lot of credit. He's been a great governor, Chris Sununu.”
pageContext.analysis: There seems to be no basis for Trump's claim. New Hampshire's unemployment rate was on the decline, and its population was growing, when Sununu was elected.
